M|1. U|**Pr|Not enough sample to detect realistic effects
M|1. U|fix|Be realistic abt MDE, get more traffic, or don't tst
M|2. O|**Pr|Waiting for sample size when you already have significance
M|2. O|fix|This is actually fine—you committed to sample size, honor it
M|3. W|**Pr|Using wrong conversion rate for calculation
M|3. W|fix|Use the specific metric and page, not site-wide averages
M|4. I|**Pr|Calculating for full traffic, then analyzing segments
M|4. I|fix|If you plan segment al, calculate sample for smallest segment
M|5. T|**Pr|Dividing traffic too many ways
M|5. T|fix|Prioritize ruthlessly, run fewer concurrent tests
M|5. T|tx|---
M|When|Opti|
M|When|1. *|Accept only detecting larger effects (20%+ lift)
M|When|2. *|Use 90% instead of 95% (risky, document it)
M|When|3. *|tst only the most promising variant
M|When|4. *|tst across multiple similar pages
M|When|5. *|tst earlier in funnel where traffic is higher
M|When|6. *|Make decision based on qualitative data instead
M|When|7. *|Accept longer duration (weeks/months)
